Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # 1. Install Python 3, pip and pytest
    apt-get update -y
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # 2. Prepare initial directory structure and files
    mkdir -p /home/user/insecure_config
    chmod 0777 /home/user        # Allow the unprivileged runtime user to write within /home/user

    # Create the insecure sshd_config with the required two lines
    cat >/home/user/insecure_config/sshd_config <<'EOF'
PermitRootLogin yes
PasswordAuthentication yes
EOF

    chmod 0644 /home/user/insecure_config/sshd_config
    chmod 0755 /home/user/insecure_config

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author hardening-task-builder
    Description "Environment for security hardening automation task. Includes pytest and the initial insecure sshd_config setup."

%help
This container provides the starting point for the security-hardening automation
exercise.  It contains:
  • /home/user/insecure_config/sshd_config with two insecure directives.
  • Python 3 and pytest for automated verification.